69th Legislature 2025 SB 263.1
1 SENATE BILL NO. 263
2 INTRODUCED BY B. BEARD
3
4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING STATE OWNERSHIP OF LESSEE WATER RIGHTS
5 USED ON STATE LANDS; REVISING AUTHORIZED IMPROVEMENT ON STATE LANDS RELATED TO
6 WATER RIGHTS; PROVIDING FOR RESTRICTIONS ON STATE OWNERSHIP OF WATER RIGHTS;
7 PROVIDING FOR DEPARTMENT REPORTING; PROVIDING RULEMAKING AUTHORITY; AMENDING
8 SECTION 77-6-301, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN IMMEDIATE EFFECTIVE DATE.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 Section 1. Section 77-6-301, MCA, is amended to read:
13 "77-6-301. Improvements authorized. (1) A lessee of state lands may place upon on the lands a
14 reasonable amount of improvements directly related to conservation of the land or necessary for proper
15 utilization of it. These improvements may consist of fences, cultivation, improvement of the land itself, irrigation
16 ditches, sheds, wells, reservoirs, water rights, and similar improvements.
17 (2) A water right owner with a state land lease may put water from a well or developed spring with
18 a ground water development works located on private land to beneficial use on state trust land for the duration
19 of a state land lease. The lessee may remove associated stock tanks and other stock water improvements
20 without authorization from the department."
21
22 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Restrictions on state ownership of water right -- department
23 reporting. (1) Except as provided in 85-2-441(2)(b) and unless authorized by the board pursuant to subsection
24 (2) of this section, the department may not obtain an ownership interest in:
25 (a) a water right or the ground water development works of a water right that is diverted from a well
26 or developed spring located on private land and put to beneficial use on state trust land; or
27 (b) a water right owned by lessee of state lands.
28 (2) (a) The department shall notify the lessee or water right owner of the department's intention to
